<rss version="2.0" xmlns:dc="http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/"><channel><title>救生艇新闻：博客——保护人类</title><link>https://lifeboat.com/blog/</link><description></description><lastBuildDate>Fri, 06 Mar 2026 01:12:10 GMT</lastBuildDate><generator>rfeed v1.1.1</generator><docs>https://github.com/svpino/rfeed/blob/master/README.md</docs><item><title>大麻提取物可显着减轻肌筋膜疼痛</title><link>https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/03/cannabis-extracts-significantly-reduce-myofascial-pain</link><description>“这些发现表明大麻素作为治疗 TMD 的一种有前途的治疗替代品的临床潜力......”[ &lt;img src="https://lifeboat.com/blog.images/cannabis-extracts-significantly-reduce-myofascial-pain.jpg" /&gt;</description><pubDate>Fri, 06 Mar 2026 01:12:06 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/03/cannabis-extracts-significantly-reduce-myofascial-pain</guid></item><item><title>黑猩猩对水晶的热爱可以帮助我们了解我们的祖先对这些石头的迷恋</title><link>https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/03/chimps-love-for-crystals-could-help-us-understand-our-own-ancestors-fascination-with-these-stones</link><description>在考古遗址中，人们多次在人属遗骸旁边发现了晶体。有证据表明，古人类收集这些石头的历史已有 78 万年之久。然而，我们知道我们的祖先并没有将它们用作武器、工具，甚至珠宝。那么他们为什么要收集它们呢？ &lt;img src="https://lifeboat.com/blog.images/chimps-love-for-crystals-could-help-us-understand-our-own-ancestors-fascination-with-these-stones.jpg" /&gt;</description><pubDate>Fri, 06 Mar 2026 00:57:06 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/03/chimps-love-for-crystals-could-help-us-understand-our-own-ancestors-fascination-with-these-stones</guid></item><item><title>古希腊最著名的神谕只是烟雾缭绕</title><link>https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/03/ancient-greeces-most-famous-oracle-was-just-high-on-gas-fumes</link><description>&lt;img src="https://politepol.com/fd/NjxHZtldG2if.xml" /&gt;</description><pubDate>Fri, 06 Mar 2026 00:42:06 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/03/ancient-greeces-most-famous-oracle-was-just-high-on-gas-fumes</guid></item><item><title>硅量子计算</title><link>https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/03/silicon-quantum-computing</link><description>SQC 生产自然界完美的量子位：磷原子精确放置在纯硅中，即 14|15 量子位平台。我们拥有全球最高精度的内部制造实践，运行精度为 0.13 纳米。&lt;img src="https://lifeboat.com/blog.images/silicon-quantum-computing.jpg" /&gt;</description><pubDate>Fri, 06 Mar 2026 00:27:06 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/03/silicon-quantum-computing</guid></item><item><title>CERN 测试下一代对撞机的量子微线探测器</title><link>https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/03/cern-tests-quantum-microwire-detectors-for-next-generation-colliders</link><description>&lt;img src="https://politepol.com/fd/NjxHZtldG2if.xml" /&gt;</description><pubDate>Fri, 06 Mar 2026 00:12:06 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/03/cern-tests-quantum-microwire-detectors-for-next-generation-colliders</guid></item><item><title>除了淀粉样斑块：人工智能揭示了阿尔茨海默氏症大脑中隐藏的化学变化</title><link>https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/03/beyond-amyloid-plaques-ai-reveals-hidden-chemical-changes-across-the-alzheimers-brain</link><description>莱斯大学的科学家制作了第一个完整的、无染料的阿尔茨海默氏症大脑分子图谱。通过将激光成像与机器学习相结合，他们发现了在大脑中不均匀分布并延伸到淀粉样蛋白斑块之外的化学变化。关键记忆区域显示胆固醇和能量相关分子发生了重大变化。研究结果表明，阿尔茨海默病是一种全脑代谢紊乱，而不仅仅是蛋白质问题。 &lt;img src="https://lifeboat.com/blog.images/beyond-amyloid-plaques-ai-reveals-hidden-chemical-changes-across-the-alzheimers-brain2.webp" /&gt;</description><pubDate>Thu, 05 Mar 2026 23:57:06 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/03/beyond-amyloid-plaques-ai-reveals-hidden-chemical-changes-across-the-alzheimers-brain</guid></item><item><title>工作的终结：Vinod Khosla 的大胆人工智能预测</title><link>https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/03/the-end-of-work-vinod-khoslas-bold-ai-prediction</link><description>&lt;img src="https://politepol.com/fd/NjxHZtldG2if.xml" /&gt;</description><pubDate>Thu, 05 Mar 2026 23:42:06 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/03/the-end-of-work-vinod-khoslas-bold-ai-prediction</guid></item><item><title>大脑疼痛和痛苦的解剖结构及其临床意义</title><link>https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/03/the-anatomy-of-pain-and-suffering-in-the-brain-and-its-clinical-implications</link><description>疼痛是一种与实际或潜在的组织损伤相关的不愉快的感觉和情感体验。慢性疼痛的患病率高达 20-30%，是全世界人类痛苦的主要原因，因为尚未开发出有效、特异性和安全的治疗方法。它在性别之间分布不均，女性经历更多的痛苦和磨难。慢性疼痛可以在解剖学和现象学上分为三个可分离但相互作用的通路：外侧“疼痛”通路、内侧“痛苦”通路和下行疼痛抑制通路。一个人可能有痛苦（充实）而没有痛苦，也可能有痛苦而没有痛苦（充实）。疼痛感通过认知、情感和自主处理导致痛苦，并表现为愤怒、恐惧、沮丧、焦虑和抑郁。 &lt;img src="https://lifeboat.com/blog.images/the-anatomy-of-pain-and-suffering-in-the-brain-and-its-clinical-implications.jpg" /&gt;</description><pubDate>Thu, 05 Mar 2026 23:27:06 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/03/the-anatomy-of-pain-and-suffering-in-the-brain-and-its-clinical-implications</guid></item><item><title>使用皮肤上的微小波纹来监测以下可能的健康问题</title><link>https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/03/using-tiny-ripples-at-skin-level-to-monitor-for-possible-health-problems-below</link><description>&lt;img src="https://politepol.com/fd/NjxHZtldG2if.xml" /&gt;</description><pubDate>Thu, 05 Mar 2026 23:12:06 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/03/using-tiny-ripples-at-skin-level-to-monitor-for-possible-health-problems-below</guid></item><item><title>功能性光声显微镜通过追踪红细胞实现超分辨率</title><link>https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/03/functional-photoacoustic-microscopy-reaches-super-resolution-by-tracking-red-blood-cells</link><description>大脑依靠微血管实时输送氧气和营养物质，微血管像电线一样穿过神经组织。虽然现代成像技术允许研究人员追踪大脑中单个神经元的活动，但它们还不够先进，无法在可比较的空间尺度上剖析微血管功能。这一差距阻碍了我们对脑小血管疾病及其对认知障碍和痴呆的影响的理解。 &lt;img src="https://lifeboat.com/blog.images/functional-photoacoustic-microscopy-reaches-super-resolution-by-tracking-red-blood-cells.jpg" /&gt;</description><pubDate>Thu, 05 Mar 2026 22:57:06 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/03/functional-photoacoustic-microscopy-reaches-super-resolution-by-tracking-red-blood-cells</guid></item></channel></rss>